            "created_at": "2011-06-28T11:14:32Z",
            "updated_at": "2011-06-28T11:23:34Z",
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "By methods you mean the HTTP methods? I'm not sure I would like to see some naming convention of class methods to handle RESTful views. These conventions should be provided by subclasses.\n\nPersonally I would like to see `__call__` being used for incoming requests, and some `__new__` stuff in the base class to achieve thread safety. See https://github.com/zacharyvoase/django-clsview/blob/master/src/djclsview.py\n\nBut that's just me!\n"
